When re-importing a GitHub project, after an initial import has been done already, changes in comments for already imported issues are ignored. The problem here is that the importer doesn't deny the re-import but also doesn't throw a warning or hint that the fresh import was not complete.

Therefore the importer cannot guarantee a reliable link between the two issue tracking systems, and besides a one-time import further use of it may cause inconsistencies.

Either a clear message by the Jira importer should be thrown, or the re-import feature should be amended to fully process updates on already imported issues.
